Ah, a classic least common multiple problem!  Finding the LCM of 9 and 60 will tell us when these events coincide again.  The LCM is the smallest number divisible by both 9 and 60.  In this case, the LCM is 180. This means it will take 180 days for Arnold to water and feed his plants on the same day. Since there are 7 days in a week, 180 days is equivalent to 25 weeks and 5 days. Counting 5 days from Tuesday brings us to Sunday. 


\begin{center}
$\boxed{\text{Sunday}}$
